article.headline: Norfolk State 52, Hampton 51
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Isaiah Coleman was fouled as he made his only basket of the game with 7 seconds left Thursday night and he converted the three-point play, providing the 16th and final lead change as Norfolk State beat Hampton 52-51. The Spartans (9-15, 8-6 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) trailed 51-49 after a free throw by Hampton's Rashad West with 20 seconds to play before Coleman was hit by Adrian Woodard as he laid in the tying basket. Coleman had missed a tying free throw with 24 seconds left, but made the big one and Norfolk State barely held on. Woodard turned the ball over for Hampton (11-11, 9-5) after Coleman's free throw, but Brian Faulcon twice missed the front end of one-and-one free throws for the Spartans in the final seconds, but the Pirates ran out of time to tie it or get the victory. Tony Murphy led Norfolk State with 17 points, but missed 18 of 22 shots from the field, including 10 of 11 3-point tries. Karandick Ogunride scored 11 points. The Pirates got 15 points from West and 10 from Bruce Brown.
